    <section id="sec:checkstyle_configuration">
        <title>Configuration</title>
        <para>See the <apilink class="org.gradle.api.plugins.quality.CheckstyleExtension"/> class in the API documentation.</para>
    </section>

    <section id="sec:checkstyle_customize_xsl">
        <title>Customizing the HTML report</title>
        <para>The HTML report generated by the <apilink class="org.gradle.api.plugins.quality.Checkstyle"/> task
            can be customized using a XSLT stylesheet, for example to highlight specific errors or change its
            appearance:
        </para>
        <sample id="customizeCheckstyleReport" dir="codeQuality" title="Customizing the HTML report">
            <sourcefile file="build.gradle" snippet="customize-checkstyle-report"/>
        </sample>
        <para>
            <ulink url="https://github.com/checkstyle/contribution/tree/master/xsl">View a sample Checkstyle stylesheet.</ulink>
        </para>
    </section>

</chapter>
